at dominate the research enterprise. Contributors are prominent international scholars in the fields of linguistics, literature, and philology: Dawn Archer, Birte Bös, Laurel Brinton, Gabriella Del Lungo Camiciotti, James Fitzmaurice, Susan Fitzmaurice, Monika Fludernik, Andreas Jucker, Thomas Kohnen, Ursula Lenker, Lynne Magnusson, and Irma Taavitsainen.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aDiscourse analysis. 0aEnglish languagexHistory. 0aHistorical linguistics. 0aPragmatics. 0aSpeech acts (Linguistics). 4aDiskursanalyse. 4aKorpora. 4aMethodologie. 4aPragmatik (Sprache). 4aSprachwandel. 4acorpora. 4adiscourse analysis. 4alanguage change. 4amethodology. 4apragmatics (language). 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aLanguage change.  acorpora.  adiscourse analysis.  amethodology.  apragmatics (language).1 aArcher, Dawn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrinton, Laurel J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBös, Birte, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDel Lungo Camiciotti, Gabriella, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFitzmaurice, James, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFitzmaurice, Susan M., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFitzmaurice, Susan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFludernik, Monika, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJucker, Andreas H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKohnen, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLenker, Ursula, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMagnusson, L